About the University
summary: Zayed University is a national and regional leader in educational innovation. Founded in 1998 and proudly bearing the name of the Founder of the Nation – the late Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan, this flagship institution has met the President’s high expectations. Today, Zayed University has two modern campuses in Dubai and Abu Dhabi that welcome both national and international students.

title: Zayed University Research
summary: The Zayed University Office of Research supports many programs designed to enhance the research culture at Zayed University, by supporting quality research that creates new knowledge in all areas of endeavor.

title: Colleges
summary: Zayed University offers globally recognized bachelor degrees in Arts and Sciences, Business, Education, IT and Media. Our graduates are bi-lingual in English and Arabic, globally and culturally aware, prepared for leadership roles, and ready to meet the challenges of the twenty-first century.

title: Zayed University appoints Knowledge E as publisher of Arab Journal of Nutrition & Exercise (ISSN 2518-6590)
summary: Zayed University and Knowledge E announced today that an agreement has been reached in which Knowledge E will take over the electronic hosting and publishing of Zayed University’s journal Arab Journal of Nutrition & Exercise (ISSN 2518-6590). In response to growing regional interest in this interdisciplinary field that bridges nutrition and exercise – both hot topics in the Arab region – the journal will be published online and welcomes submissions of new manuscripts from fellow academics who are seeking a suitable journal to disseminate their findings. Under the conditions of the agreement, Knowledge E will begin publishing the journal immediately including all previous issues back to Vol. 1 Issue 1.

title: Archaeology Field School and Archaeology Club
summary: “Our mission as faculty is not only to transfer knowledge theoretically to the students, but also to teach them skills on how to conduct archaeological research”, said Dr. Timothy Power, Associate Professor, College of Humanities and Social Sciences. Soon after he joined ZU in 2014, Dr. Tim formed both the Archaeology Field School and Archaeology Club to involve female undergraduates in a series of national archaeological research projects.  Turning some courses in the Emirati Studies major such as Archaeological Field School, Independent Study and Special Topics into a feasible research projects has not only allowed these young female Emirati to discover their own history but also prepared them to become the first cohort of national archaeologists. “All the projects we are involved in try to shed light on the 17th to 20th century era, when the tribes started to settle in the Trucial States and form alliances creating the modern history of the UAE” remarked Dr. Tim.

title: Zayed University launches new research centre to transform Arabic teaching and learning
summary: Zayed University today announced the launch of the Zai Centre, a pioneering new research centre focused on Arabic teaching and learning. Zai will be the first academic institution in the UAE to look at how Arabic is taught around the world. Led by internationally acclaimed academic Dr Hanada Taha Thomure, ZAI will identify best practice for teaching Arabic and develop the tools to empower teachers enabling them to inspire their students. Zai will also provide parents with guidance on how they can ensure that their children are able to improve their Arabic at home from a young age.

Turkish President Abdullah Gul visited Zayed University's  new campus in Abu Dhabi on Monday, January 30, 2012.

summary: Vice President and Prime Minister and Ruler of Dubai His Highness Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum received in the Dubai Government Media Office today a number of female students of Information College of Zayed University (ZU), who called to acquaint with the media work mechanism and message of the office.

title: H.E. Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan inaugurates Zayed University's du multimedia lab
summary: H.E Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, and President of Zayed University, inaugurated the du multimedia lab at Zayed University in Dubai, on 22 February 2012. Also in attendance was Osman Sultan – CEO of du, VIPs, and senior officials from Zayed University and du.

title: H.E. Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan inaugurates the 4th "Women as Global Leaders" conference 2012
summary: Under the Patronage of Her Highness, Sheikha Fatima Bint Mubarak, Mother of the Nation, His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, inaugurated the 4th "Women as Global Leaders" conference 2012 in Zayed University Abu Dhabi.

title: His Highness Sheikh Majid Bin Mohammed Bin Rashid Al Maktoum inaugurates Zayed University Carnival
summary: His Highness Sheikh Majid bin Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Chairman of Dubai Culture and Arts  inaugurated the "Zayed University Carnival 2012” at the University’s campus in Dubai on March 6, 2012.

title: Humaid Bin Nasser Al Owais Establishes an Endowed Professorship  in Arabic Language for AED 5 Million
summary: H.E. Humaid Bin Nasser Al Owais, the Former UAE Minister of  Electricity and Water, made  a donation of AED 5 Million for the first endowed professorship in Arabic language. The Humaid Bin Nasser Al Owais Professorship in Arabic Language will make it possible for a scholar to focus on topics related to the Arabic language.

title: Zayed University offers new Programs at GETEX 2012
summary: During the opening of Gulf Education & Training Exhibition “GETEX 2012” that is held Under the Patronage of His Excellency Sheikh Nahyan Bin Mubarak Al Nahyan, Minister of Higher, Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, the Zayed University’s booth participating in the exhibition introduces new programs that are offered for the first time this year.

title: Zayed University inaugurates the  "Khalaf Al Habtoor Assistive Technology Resource Center"
summary: H.E. Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University inaugurated the “Khalaf Al Habtoor Assistive Technology Resource Center” for students with special needs at Zayed University Dubai Campus during the launch ceremony held in the presence of Khalaf Al Habtoor, the founder of Al Habtoor Group of Companies, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President, Zayed University, Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost Zayed University, Safia Al Raqbani, Chief Development and External Affairs Officer, faculty, staff and public figures.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan inaugurates Sculpture Exhibition "Jothoor & Shumookh"
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, inaugurated Zayed Univeristy Abu Dhabi’s suculpture exhibition, entitled “ Jothoor and Shumookh”, and presented by the Saudi artist Abdul- Hafez bin Jamah Al-Ghamdi.

title: ZU Vice President actively contributes to the Arab Media Forum 2012
summary: Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, took part in the 11th Edition of the Arab Media Forum 2012, which was held under the Patronage and in the Presence of His Highness Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashed Al Maktoum, Vice President and Prime Minister and Ruler of Dubai.

title: His Excellency  Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan attends the first Zayed University Alumni Reunion
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University,  recently attended the Zayed University Alumni Reunion in  celebration of the 10th Graduation Anniversary of the first Zayed University Cohort 2002 in the new Abu Dhabi Campus.

title: French Book Donation to Zayed University
summary: Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice-President of Zayed University, praised the collaboration with the cultural, educational and scientific institutions in France, expressing his hope that this collaboration will enhance opportunities for scientific and cultural exchange between Zayed University and those institutions.

title: HE Sheikh Nahayan signs agreement to set up the Ahmad Seddiqi Professorship in Arabic language at Zayed University
summary:
HE Sheikh Nahayan signs agreement to set up the Ahmad Seddiqi Professorship in Arabic language at Zayed University.

H.E Sheikh Nahayan signed the agreement with Abdul Hameed Ahmad Siddiqi, who was representing Ahmad Siddiqi and Sons.

title: HE Sheikh Nahayan signs agreement to set up Sheikh Salem bin Ham Al Amri Professorship in Islamic Legal Theory at Zayed University
summary:
HE Sheikh Nahayan signs agreement to set up Sheikh Salem bin Ham Al Amri Professorship in Islamic Legal Theory at Zayed University.

Present were Ahmed Humaid Al Tayer, Head of the Supervising Committee over the endowment fund at Zayed University, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, Safia Al Raqbani, Chief Development and External Affairs Officer, and other officials.

title: HE Sheikh Nahayan signs agreement on setting up Obaid Al Helu Professorship in Islamic Jurisprudence at Zayed University
summary:
HE Sheikh Nahayan signs agreement on setting up Obaid Al Helu Professorship in Islamic Jurisprudence at the Islamic World Studies Institute at Zayed University, at the residence of Al Hellou in Dubai.

Present were Ahmed Humaid Al Tayer, Head of the Supervising Committee over the endowment fund at Zayed University, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, Safia Al Raqbani, Chief Development and External Affairs Officer, and other dignitaries.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Attends The iPad Executive Briefing at Zayed University
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education& Scientific Research, President of Zayed University,‬ stated that e-learning tops the priority list of the UAE education development strategy, especially in light of the National initiative to distribute 14,000 iPads amongst new students enrolled in Zayed University, UAEU and HCT.‬

title: Zayed University Celebrates the Third International White Cane Day
summary: Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Zayed University's Vice President, inaugurated the Third International Annual White Cane Day at Zayed University’s Dubai Campus on October 14, 2012. This event organized by the Office of Accessibility, in the presence of Dr. Larry Wilson, Zayed University’s Provost, and a number of public figures, and Zayed University students, faculty and staff.

title: Zayed University signs an endowment agreement with Union National Bank to create a Union National Bank Professorship in Banking
summary: Union National Bank, signed an Endowment Agreement with Zayed University to establish a Professorship at Zayed University titled "Union National Bank Professorship in Banking". UNB will contribute an amount of Five Million Dirhams over a period of five years to establish this Professorship in Banking.

title: Zayed University hosts its 15th Annual Convocation in Abu Dhabi
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University reflected on the various components that will leverage Zayed University’s position amongst Top international education institutions,

title: H.E Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan chairs the first meeting of the Higher Education Coordinating Council
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, chaired the first meeting of the Higher Education Coordinating Council at Zayed University’s Abu Dhabi campus earlier today. Amongst the attendees were Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, Dr. Ali Rashid Al Noaimi, Vice Chancellor of UAEU, and Dr. Tayyib Kamali, Vice Chancellor of the Higher Colleges of Technology (HCT).

title: Zayed University Celebrates the UAE's 41st National Day
summary: Zayed University’s campuses in both Dubai and Abu Dhabi dedicated Wednesday the 28th and Thursday the 29th of November 2012 to offer thanks and gratitude for 41 years of unity in the UAE.

title: Ravi Zacharias visits Zayed University Campus in Abu Dhabi
summary: Ravi Zackarias lectured to Zayed University administrators, guests, faculty, staff and students on November 26 in the Sheikha Fatima Theater in the Convention Center.

title: Zayed University's Institute for the Arabic Language offers new academic programs
summary: Zayed University announced yesterday the new academic programs that are offered through the Institute for the Arabic Language. The initiative comes from the continuous effort by the University to advance the leadership role it plays in supporting the Arabic Language and strengthen its position to tackle the challenges the language faces in this globalized era.

title: H.E Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan inaugurates the 3rd Emirati-Swiss Friendship Forum
summary: Leading experts from the UAE and Switzerland were brought together at Zayed University Abu Dhabi, by the third meeting of Emirati-Swiss Friendship Forum, which saw participants debate on issues related to water sustainability.

title: Zayed University Council meets under the chairmanship of H.E Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan
summary: Zayed University Council held a meeting this morning under the chairmanship of His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research President of Zayed University, and in the presence of the council members Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, and Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost of Zayed University.

title: British Prime Minister David Cameron visits Zayed University Campus in Abu Dhabi
summary: H.E Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, welcomed British Prime Minister David Cameron to Zayed University’s Abu Dhabi Campus yesterday. Also present were Sheikh Shakhbout bin Nahyan Al Nahyan, Dr. Anwar Mohammed Gargash, Minister of State for Foreign Affairs, Dominic Jermey, the British Ambassador to the UAE, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost of Zayed University, and a number of officials, Zayed University faculty and students.

title: Zayed University celebrates the graduation of its 11th cohort
summary: Zayed University celebrated the graduation of its 11th cohort last Thursday December 6, 2012 on the new Abu Dhabi campus, where His Highness Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, handed 890 graduates their diplomas in the presence of Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, Dr. Larry Wilson , Provost of Zayed University, and a number of faculty and staff members and families of the graduates.

title: Zayed University's  Student Council in Abu Dhabi honors the UAE National Football team
summary: Zayed University’s Student Council in Abu Dhabi honored the UAE  National Football team this morning on the occasion of winning the 21st Gulf Cup, which was held in Bahrain recently. A celebration was held on Zayed University’s Abu Dhabi campus to acknowledge this great achievement in the presence of players Ismail Matar and Hamdan Al Kamali.

title: Zayed University honors laborers working on its campuses
summary: In support of the “Thank You” initiative launched across the UAE by His Highness Sheikh Mohammed Bin Rashed Al Maktoum, Vice President and Prime Minister of the UAE and Ruler of Dubai, to present thanks and appreciation to laborers working in public services,  Zayed University organized a ceremony in the honor of laborers working on its campuses, where Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, praised the valuable work that laborers are committing to and their genuine contribution to the betterment of the society.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan oversees the strategies and programs of the Dubai Autism Center
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, praised the efforts of the employees and specialists working at the Dubai Autism Center, which offers various services targeted towards encouraging a better understanding of Autism and providing specialist services for people with Autism and those who care for them.

title: Pink Caravan concludes its pan-UAE journey at Zayed University
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, President of Zayed University, and HE Sheikha Lubna bint Khalid Al Qasimi, Minister of Foreign Trade, attended the closing ceremony of the Pink Caravan’s annual ride, the pan-UAE breast cancer awareness and detection initiative by the Friends of Cancer Patients charitable organisation (FoCP), which was held at Zayed University in Abu Dhabi, on the 12 of February.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahyan receives Zayed University Australian students
summary: Hi Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research, and President of Zayed University, stressed on the need for international expansion of Arabic language learning programs to promote cultural cooperation and exchange of educational and scientific expertise with different countries.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan receives organizers of 7th Gulf Conference on Professional Issues
summary: Zayed University hosted the 7th Gulf Conference on Professional Issues at its Convention Center in Abu Dhabi on the 6th and 7th of February 2013. The conference was held in association with Student Affairs Administrators in Higher Education (NASPA), a leading association for the advancement, health, and sustainability of the student affairs profession, and American College Personnel Association (ACPA), and attracted 150 student administrators from the GCC and international universities.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan inaugurates Zayed University's classic cars' exhibition
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth and Community Development, President of Zayed University, inaugurated the classic cars’ exhibition that was organized by Zayed University’s French Club students, as part of the annual francophone celebrations. His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan toured around the exhibition that was held on Abu Dhabi campus, accompanied by HE Ahmad Humaid Al Tayer, HE Khaldoon Al Mubarak, Dr. Maryam Al Rumaithi, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, and Dr. Larry Wilson. The exhibition showcased very rare and valuable cars that were produced in the 1920s.

title: H.E. Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan inaugurates the "Lest We Forget: Emirati Vernacular Photography" exhibition
summary: H.E. Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, U.A.E. Minister of Culture and President of Zayed University inaugurated the “Lest We Forget: Emirati Vernacular Photography” exhibition on Zayed University Abu Campus last Thursday.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan launches the world's biggest stamp to honor the Mother of the Nation
summary: is Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth and Community Development, President of Zayed University, launched the biggest stamp in the world to honor the Mother of the Nation, Her Highness Sheikha Fatima Bint Mubarak, Chairman of the Family Development Foundation and the head of the General Women's Union, on Zayed University Campus Abu Dhabi

title: His Highness Sheikh Mansoor bin Mohammed bin Rashed Al Maktoum visits Zayed University's Annual Carnival
summary: His Highness Sheikh Mansoor bin Mohammed bin Rashed Al Maktoum visited Zayed University’s Annual Carnival, which was held on Dubai Campus, in the presence of Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost of Zayed University, and Zayed University students, faculty and staff.

title: His Highness Sheikh Majid Bin Mohammed Al Maktoum Inaugurates the Zayed University Carnival 2013 in Dubai
summary: His Highness Sheikh Majid Bin Mohammed Bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Chairman of Dubai Culture and Arts inaugurated the Zayed University Carnival 2013 held at Zayed University’s Dubai Campus with a generous sponsorship from His Highness Sheikh Majid.

title: Zayed University Dubai organizes Careers Spotlight 2013
summary: His Excellency Ahmed Humaid Al Tayer, Head of the Supervising Committee over the endowment fund at Zayed University, unveiled the University’s Careers Spotlight 2013  on Dubai campus last Tuesday, in the presence of Mr. Juma Khalifa Al Naboodah, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost of Zayed University, and a number of Zayed University officials, faculty, staff, students and alumni.

title: Zayed University becomes the first institution outside the UK to be accredited for the UK matrix standard award in career guidance
summary: Zayed University’s Career Services have been awarded the matrix Standard for information, advice and guidance. This followed an external assessment process undertaken by emqc Ltd, the organization responsible for the management, administration and delivery of the matrix Standard. This award highlights Zayed University’s continued commitment to deliver career programs and services that meet internationally recognized quality standards.

title: Four- Time World Boxing Champion Laila Ali visits Zayed University Campus in Abu Dhabi
summary: Laila Ali, Daughter of Legendary Boxer Mohammed Ali and Four-Time World Boxing Champion, gave an enlightening talk in front of Zayed University students, faculty and staff, about the importance of leading active and healthy lifestyles, during her visit to Zayed University Campus in Abu Dhabi earlier today.

title: Zayed University students raise Dh 109,606 for displaced Syrians
summary: Zayed University students have collected about Dh109,606  for the displaced Syrians during the charity campaign “Action 2013” that took place on Zayed University Abu Dhabi Campus last week.

title: Zayed University launches the UAE National Film Library and Archive, and ZUMEFF
summary: Zayed University will officially launch the UAE National Film Library and Archive (UNFLA) today, under the patronage and in the presence of His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth and Community Development. The first of its kind in the Gulf, the archive will be a permanent home for the work of Emirati funded and made films for generations to come.

title: Grand Imam of Al-Azhar visits Zayed University
summary: The Grand Imam of Al-Azhar Dr. Ahmed Al Tayyeb said Zayed University has the adequate resources to make a scientific, academic and cultural breakthrough in the UAE.

title: Dubai Government Human Resources Department signs MoU with Zayed University
summary: Her Highness Sheikha Latifa Bint Mohammed Bin Rashid Al Maktoum, member of the Board of Trustees of the Emirates Literature Foundation, said that the launch of “National Programme to Build Talent” reflects the massive efforts of the Dubai government to enhance the skills and knowledge of Emirati women graduates through exceptional educational experience provided by a great educational firm such as Zayed University.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan signs an agreement to establish "Abdul Ghaffar Hussain Professorship in Arabic Literature" at Zayed University
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth, and Community Development, emphasized on the importance of Islamic Waqf (endowment) and its characteristics as a unique association that has noble and social goals, and which has valuable benefits in the Islamic world today.

title: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan inaugurates "Hear my Voice - Understanding Hearing Loss" conference at Zayed University
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth, and Community Development, inaugurated the "Hear my Voice Understanding Hearing Loss" conference that is held under His Excellency’s patronage and organized by Zayed University and "Kalimati Speech & Communication Center" at the Zayed University Dubai campus. The two-day conference attracts many international speakers and health care professionals, representative from several hospitals and clinics dealing with hearing impairment, UAE & GCC Deaf Associations and the UAE Deaf community.

title: Zayed University organizes a conference about "The State of the Social, Humanitarian, and Islamic sciences in Arab and Western Academia"
summary: Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University gave the Opening speech on behalf of His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mubarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth, and Community Development, during the conference “The State of the Social, Humanitarian, and Islamic sciences in Arab and Western Academia” organized by Institute of Islamic World Studies at Zayed University in Dubai, which is hosting more than 20 well-known international speakers.

title: Zayed University honors outstanding students
summary: In the presence of Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice-President, and Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost, and a great circle of faculty, administrative staff, and students, Zayed University has today celebrated in an honorary ceremony the outstanding academic achievements of its top students for AY 2012-2013.

title: His Highness Dr Sheikh Sultan Bin Mohammed Al Qasimi honors Zayed University
summary: On the sidelines of the honoring ceremony of 11th Sharjah Prize for Best PhD Thesis in Administration 2012-2013 held at Sharjah University’s campus, His Highness Dr. Sheikh Sultan Bin Mohammed Al Qasimi, Supreme Council Member and Ruler of Sharjah, honored Zayed University, represented by its Vice-President, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim  and accompanying delegation, for Zayed University’s   remarkable academic and educational cooperation. His Highness presented to Zayed University’s VP a memorable shield to mark Zayed University’s continuous support and tremendous multi-cultural  and educational contributions.

title: His Highness Sheikh Nahayan congratulates Zayed University students on winning an international journalistic excellence award
summary: His Highness Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth and Community Development, President of Zayed University, congratulated Zayed University’s Zajel editorial team on winning an international journalistic excellence award that was granted by the Society for  Professional Journalists, during his visit to Zayed University Abu Dhabi's newsroom which was set up by "TwoFour 54".

title: H.E Sheikh Nahayan instructs ECLC to adopt advanced learning solutions
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth and Community Development, President of Zayed University toured around  Zayed University’s Early Childhood  Learning Center in Abu Dhabi, in the presence of H.E Ahmad Humaid Al Tayer, Head of the Supervising Committee over the endowment fund at Zayed University, H.E Khaldoon Khalifa Al Mubarak, Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director of Mubadala, Dr. Maryam Al Rumaithi, the Family Development Foundation's Director General, H.E Ali Al Ketbi, Deputy General Secretary of the Public Administration Directorate, General Secretariat of the Executive Council, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, and Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost of Zayed University.

title: Zayed University Council approves new policies
summary: Zayed University Council held a meeting under the chairmanship of His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of UAE Culture, Youth and Community Development, President of Zayed University, and in the presence of the council members,  H.E Ahmad Humaid Al Tayer, Head of the Supervising Committee over the endowment fund at Zayed University, H.E Khaldoon  Khalifa Al Mubarak, Chief  Executive Officer and Managing Director of Mubadala, Dr. Maryam Al Rumaithi, the Family Development Foundation's Director General, H.E Ali Al Ketbi, Deputy General Secretary of the Public Administration Directorate, General Secretariat of the Executive Council, Dr. Sulaiman Al Jassim, Vice President of Zayed University, and Dr. Larry Wilson, Provost of Zayed University,

title: Zayed University Hosts the "Emirati Young Women Entrepreneur Leadership Forum"
summary: Under the patronage of H.H Sheikha Latifa Bint Mohammed Bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Board Member Emirates Literature Foundation, Zayed University hosted the “Emirati Young Women Entrepreneur Leadership Forum” which addressed the role of women leaders in the development of the entrepreneurial spirit in the United Arab Emirates, on its Dubai campus. The conference aimed to inspire, educate and encourage female ZU students to become future global leaders in the United Arab Emirates and the broader Gulf Cooperation Council countries. It also provided students with an opportunity to connect with distinguished UAE business and to learn from their experiences.

title: H.E Sheikh Nahayan officially inaugurates the National Film Library at Zayed University
summary: His Excellency Sheikh Nahayan Mabarak Al Nahayan, Minister of Culture, Youth and Community Development, inaugurated the UAE National Film Library and Archive (UNFLA) on Tuesday, April 30, 2013.  The new library is located in a state-of-the-art archive room housed in Zayed University Library, Abu Dhabi Campus

title: His Highness Sheikh Majid Bin Mohammed praises the artworks exhibited at EDGE Exhibition
summary: His Highness Sheikh Majid Bin Mohammed Bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Chairman of Dubai Culture and Arts Authority, praised the artworks displayed at the EDGE Exhibition, and which exhibited seniors projects for students from the College of Arts and Creative Enterprises at Zayed University, during His Highness’s visit at Zayed University Dubai Campus in the presence of Zayed University’s students, faculty and staff.

title: Zayed University and Hamdan bin Mohammed Heritage Center sign a Memorandum of Understanding
summary: UAE Vice President and Prime Minister and Ruler of Dubai, His Highness Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum, attended a ceremony marking the signing of three strategic agreements by the Federal Government in the field of developing abilities and skills of federal government staff.

title: Zayed University to train 100  Federal Government employees as of September 2013
summary: UAE Vice President and Prime Minister and Ruler of Dubai, His Highness Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum, attended a ceremony marking the signing of three strategic agreements by the Federal Government in the field of developing abilities and skills of federal government staff.

title: Zayed University Granted Renewal of International Accreditation
summary: The Middle States Commission on Higher Education (MSCHE) in the United States has announced that Zayed University’s full international accreditation has been reaffirmed. This reaffirmation of accreditation by the MSCHE marks Zayed University one of  a very few universities in the Middle East to achieve this status.

title: ZU Students participate in the "Multiculturalism & Leadership" Programs in Dundee.
summary: In its continuous effort to promote multi-culturalism, the Al-Maktoum College of Higher Education at Dundee-Scotland is on the go to welcome a new batch of female students from all universities of the United Arab Emirates who will participate in the 16th session of the “Multiculturalism & Leadership” program, organized by the College, August 12-. September 10, 2013.

title: Zayed university graduate awarded a Fulbright Scholarship
summary: AMIDEAST Abu Dhabi and the US- Emirati Education Committee have just concluded their annual interviews for the Fulbright Scholarship cycle 2014- 2015 and have announced, that Sarah Al Awadhi, a Zayed University Alumnae, Class of 2011, is one of two recipients who have earned this elite Scholarship.

title: H.E. Dr. Maitha AlShamsi, President of Zayed University Highlights the University's Strategy for the New Academic Year
summary: In her keynote address on the occasion of the University’s 16th convocation, and in the presence of H.E. Prof. Abdalla AlAmiri, ZU Provost along with faculty and staff,  H.E. Dr. Maitha AlShamsi, Minister of State and President of Zayed University praised the tremendous progress the university has made since its founding in 1998. During her address, H.E. Dr. Al Shamsi pointed the tremendous achievements the university has made in terms of academic recognition, services provided, and contributions to disseminate knowledge and education, in its short life span.

title: Zayed University organizes orientation week for new students
summary: Zayed University launched the “Ya Hala” orientation week today, September 2nd, on both Abu Dhabi and Dubai campuses. The two-day orientation program is expected to welcome over 3,000 female and male students, as well as their parents and/or guardians.

title: Zayed University's College of Education Granted Prominent International Accreditation

Sheikh Nahyan Mubarak Al Nahyan, Minister of Culture, Youth & Community Development, ADMAF Patron and President.

Action 2015 is a co-curricular project based on the ABP’s curriculum that has a focus on the topic of Humanitarian Aid. The aim of this service-learning project is for students, male and female, to further understand what a humanitarian crisis is and how they can by providing humanitarian relief where it is needed most.

Social Security Fund, and Professor Reyadh AlMehaideb, Vice President of Zayed University.

title: Zayed University launches new research centre to transform Arabic teaching and learning

title: Ms. Robyn Albers and Hessa Rashed AlNuaimi
summary: Ms. Robyn Albers and Hessa Rashed AlNuaimi published a paper “Korean Clubs in the United Arab Emirates: Promoting Intercultural Competence of Female Emiratis” (2020) in Business Communication Research and Practice journal. The article is about the significant impact that Hallyu, the “Korean Wave”, has recently had on young female Emiratis.  The university students are first interested in Korean pop music (K-pop) and Korean dramas (K-dramas) and then become more fascinated about learning Korean culture and language.  Therefore, they join Korea Clubs at universities across the UAE which is also providing a surprising benefit.  The strong interest in Korea, coupled with Korean cultural experiences within the UAE, is creating culturally competent students who are ready to join the workforce. Arab students capable of speaking Arabic, English, and Korean fluently with an understanding of Korean culture will benefit the on-going bilateral relations between the UAE and Korea. Learning Korean and learning about Korean culture has benefitted Hessa more than she could imagine.  She says, “Because of my victory, I also had the honor of being the Korean speaking host for the Emirati-Korean Cultural Festival which took place in the presence of Her Excellency Noura Al Kaabi, The Minister of Culture and Knowledge Development and President of Zayed University, as well as His Excellency Park Yang Woo, Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism, including other Korean Officials at Zayed University”.

title: Commodity Frontiers and Global Capitalist Expansion: Social, Ecological and Resource Policy Implications
summary: The transformation of the physical environment and, in turn, people's relationship to the environment have been key processes in the emergence and consolidation of global capitalism over the past 500 years. Providing raw and intermediate materials to satisfy the voracious appetite of machines and city dwellers, the flatlands, valleys, forests, marine spaces, and mountains of the world have been transformed at astonishing and accelerating speed. This process of appropriation of the world’s ecological surpluses has come to be understood as that of shifting ‘commodity frontiers’. The two-day multi-disciplinary workshop is designed to explore the dynamics of frontier processes and how they relate to social, economic, political and ecological change in their zones of contact, with particular interest in research that explores one or more of the following issues:

summary: The wide spread of various forms of political violence in many Arab countries has contributed to the creation and consolidation of a system of values, ideas, beliefs and attitudes that justify the use of violence in political process. summary: The Swahili Coast was closely connected with the Arabian Gulf through the seasonal monsoon. This lecture will examine the links between the two regions during the later medieval and early modern period drawing on the latest archaeological evidence.

summary: There is a two-fold fundamental issue in the African countries: The first is reflected in the “religious movement for renewal,” which has as its purpose the linking of faith with its original roots.

title: Making a Difference: Connecting research, teaching and practice in building tolerant and inclusive societies
summary: Contemporary globalization has redefined notions of time, space, distances, boundaries, and borders.  It has changed the social, economic, cultural, and political environment and the nature of global interaction.

path: https://www.zu.ac.ae/main/en/colleges/colleges/__college_of_humanities_and_social_sciences/_events_items/The Millennials Around the World A Global Generation
title: The Millennials around the world: A global generation?
summary: The Millennials those born in 1980s-1990s are coming of age in changing times.   Around the Global North, and increasingly beyond, higher education is becoming the norm, new digital technology is ubiquitous, and livelihoods and lives must be created in an interconnected global economy and cultural sphere. On many measures today’s young people (at least in many countries) are the healthiest and safest generation ever.

title: Shipwrecks, Replicas, and "Dhows"Shipwrecks, Replicas and "Dhows": Experimental Maritime Archaeology in the Indian Ocean
summary: The development of the ship, or the dhow as is it is commonly referred to in Anglophone literature, played an essential role in the expansion of seaborne trade in the pre-modern Indian Ocean. These vessels were vehicles of trade, migration and culture that connected the region in a series of maritime networks. This talk discusses recent efforts to better understand the early ships of the Arabian Gulf and Indian Ocean, with a focus on experimental maritime archaeological projects that have attempted to reconstruct and sail these vessels.

title: Developments in UAE Population & Labor Market
summary: Dr. Mouawiya will present a general overview of the UAE population, evolution of Emirati and expatriate labor forces along the main developments of the UAE private labor market.  He sheds light on the demographic imbalances, population pyramids, fertility, duration of stay, turnover ratio, internal mobility, unemployment and Emiratization.

title: CoB Students at the Student Exchange Program launched by the Ministry of Economy
summary:
"The youth are our country's most cherished asset" - this quote by His Highness Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Vice President and Prime Minister of the UAE and Ruler of Dubai, reflects the UAE wise leadership’s belief in the potential of youth. Inspired by this wise vision, today I had the pleasure of meeting a group of ambitious Emirati youth as part of the Student Exchange Program launched by the Ministry of Economy in collaboration with a number of leading national universities. Through this program, we will work to develop the potentials of youngsters who are capable of understanding the variables of the economy and foreseeing its future.
The program is a new opportunity to invest in Emirati youth and enable them to contribute to the economic growth and support the country's future vision for the next 50 years.
Youth will remain the most important and the safest bet to invest in, in order to develop the present and build the future.

title: Publication on Sustainability in Harvard Business Review (HBR online)
summary: Climate change, sustainability, and ESG considerations are increasingly taking center stage in corporate boardrooms across the world. When measuring and communicating corporate sustainability performance through sustainability reports or ratings, executives face a rapidly evolving and complex set of choices. As a result, companies are at risk of falling behind or choosing inappropriate reports and ratings that don’t drive sustainability performance and open the door to accusations of greenwashing. This article introduces the sustainability reporting matrix, a tool that helps executives and sustainability managers to focus on the sustainability reporting standards and ratings that are most closely aligned with their strategic requirements and the information needs of their stakeholders.

title: CoB Students at the Student Exchange Program launched by the Ministry of Economy
summary:
"The youth are our country's most cherished asset" - this quote by His Highness Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Vice President and Prime Minister of the UAE and Ruler of Dubai, reflects the UAE wise leadership’s belief in the potential of youth. Inspired by this wise vision, today I had the pleasure of meeting a group of ambitious Emirati youth as part of the Student Exchange Program launched by the Ministry of Economy in collaboration with a number of leading national universities. Through this program, we will work to develop the potentials of youngsters who are capable of understanding the variables of the economy and foreseeing its future.
The program is a new opportunity to invest in Emirati youth and enable them to contribute to the economic growth and support the country's future vision for the next 50 years.
Youth will remain the most important and the safest bet to invest in, in order to develop the present and build the future.

title: Publication on Sustainability in Harvard Business Review (HBR online)
summary: Climate change, sustainability, and ESG considerations are increasingly taking center stage in corporate boardrooms across the world. When measuring and communicating corporate sustainability performance through sustainability reports or ratings, executives face a rapidly evolving and complex set of choices. As a result, companies are at risk of falling behind or choosing inappropriate reports and ratings that don’t drive sustainability performance and open the door to accusations of greenwashing. This article introduces the sustainability reporting matrix, a tool that helps executives and sustainability managers to focus on the sustainability reporting standards and ratings that are most closely aligned with their strategic requirements and the information needs of their stakeholders.

title: Burnout is a psychological state
summary: Burnout is a psychological state that evolves from being constantly stressed and having stress reactions accumulated for a long period of time (Kwag & Kim, 2009). There are many determinants of job burnout such as, work overload and environmental stressors (Kwag & Kim, 2009). Employee burnout has negative consequences such as high rates employee’s absenteeism and turnover (Kwag & Kim, 2009). According to a study conduced by Robert Half UAE (2013), 64% of UAE organizations suffer from job burnout (Abbas, 2017). As a result, UAE businesses are experiencing employees moving from one company to another to find job opportunities where they can be in a less stressful working environment (Abbas, 2017).

summary: The Zayed University Urban Satellite Space (ZUUSS) is a new exhibition and project space presented in partnership with Alserkal Avenue. title: ZU Welcomed into CFA Institute University Affiliation Program
summary: CFA Institute, the global association of investment professionals, confirmed that Zayed University is the first university in Abu Dhabi and Dubai to receive an entry into the CFA Institute University Affiliation Program. The affiliation was announced at an event organized at the Zayed University Abu Dhabi campus and hosted by His Excellency Prof. Reyadh AlMehaideb, Zayed University Vice President, alongside a number of faculty members and attendees.

title: CEOx1 Shaima's day at TECOM with Dr. Amina Rostamani
summary: Shaima AlMuallem, a ZU Graduate, in her own words stated "it was such a good day, I learned a lot and I was very happy to meet Dr. Amina because she has a very different way of thinking unlike many other people that I met", as she reminisced of her experience at the CEOx1 Day that she spent with Dr. Amina Al Rustamani, the Group Chief Executive Officer of TECOM Group, a member of Dubai Holding.

title: COB hosts distinguished Professor of Accounting Dr. Miklos Vasarhelyi
summary: The College of Business at Zayed University had the privilege of inviting the KPMG Distinguished Professor of Accounting Dr. Miklos Vasarhelyi for a two-day visit on 19th – 20th November 2017.  Professor Vasarhelyi is a Professor of Accounting Information Systems and Director of Rutgers Accounting Research Center and Continuous Auditing & Reporting Lab (CAR Lab).

title: COB hosts distinguished Professor Jarrad Harford
summary: On Tuesday and Wednesday October 24th and 25th, the College of Business had a unique opportunity to host Dr. Jarrad Harford, a distinguished professor and world-renowned scholar in Corporate Finance, who conducted several professional workshops and seminars with faculty and students in both Dubai and Abu Dhabi campuses.

title: Urgent need to enable and sustain entrepreneurship
summary: Despite a climate of massive unemployment, South Africa’s post-school education system remains largely preoccupied with producing graduates who will seek jobs, according to Narend Baijnath, CEO of the Council on Higher Education. In fact, levels of entrepreneurial activity are dropping and the education sector is partly to blame.

title: The glass ceiling shows no sign of shattering soon
summary: In her 27th novel, The Cleft, ­Nobel-prize winning author Doris Lessing described a prehistoric race of semi-aquatic proto-­humans. These pre-­humans live in a world without males. Theirs is an idyllic utopia where females rule peacefully – until the first males are born.

title: A knowledge economy begins with funding for research
summary: The transformation from an oil-based economy to a knowledge-based one is not only an important priority for UAE policymakers, it should be a priority for every individual in society.

title: Burnout is a psychological state
summary: Burnout is a psychological state that evolves from being constantly stressed and having stress reactions accumulated for a long period of time (Kwag & Kim, 2009). There are many determinants of job burnout such as, work overload and environmental stressors (Kwag & Kim, 2009). Employee burnout has negative consequences such as high rates employee’s absenteeism and turnover (Kwag & Kim, 2009). According to a study conduced by Robert Half UAE (2013), 64% of UAE organizations suffer from job burnout (Abbas, 2017). As a result, UAE businesses are experiencing employees moving from one company to another to find job opportunities where they can be in a less stressful working environment (Abbas, 2017).

title: WOMENA
summary: Dubai SME, the agency of Dubai Economy mandated to develop the small and medium enterprise (SME) sector, and WOMENA have jointly launched the ‘Future Founders and Future Funders Programme’. title: Organizing seminars in the book club at the College of Humanities and Social Sciences:
summary: The "Book Club" is organizing a number of seminars led by college professors about the club's most important literary publications. The club is chaired by one of the college's faculty members in rotation, and students will select books to read individually. The books will not necessarily be from the curriculum of their college; however, the books chosen by the club are literary books and specialized magazines.

title: Poetry Session
summary: In the frame of the Reading Year Committee instructions at Zayed University, the department of the library and common learning is organizing a poetry session in November 2016, which coincides with the celebrations of UAE National Day. The session will be attended by a number of speakers, and there will be a number of other activities organized at the same time.

title: Reading at Home (Session in September 2016)
summary: A session was conducted by a Faculty member from the College of Education and organized by the Early Childhood Learning Center, addressing parents, faculty and students in the Center on the subject of “Reading at Home for your Children.” The session was also delivered by two students from the Early Childhood Learning Course EDC386.

title: Reading in Arabic Campaign
summary: The Alumni Office at Zayed University launched a campaign to promote the culture of reading in Arabic in cooperation with the Dubai International Center for Books.

title: Summer Reading Campaign (June- August 2016)
summary: The Academic Bridge Program organized a campaign to encourage students to read as many books as they can during the summer vacation.

title: Discussion of a book in Arabic Prose
summary: Distribution of the book "Arabic Prose" to discuss in the "Loqya Club" with the Department of Arabic Language at Zayed University.

title: Student Council's Open Meeting
summary: Zayed University's Student Council in Abu Dhabi organized a number of open sessions to discuss the importance of reading, how to select a book to read and the books that have most influenced the speakers. The sessions were attended by Dr.  Prof. Reyadh AlMehaideb and Sheikh Waseem Yousef, the Imam and Preacher at the Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque and others.

title: Honoring outstanding students
summary: Distribution of books by the Emarati Author Yasser Harib to honor the 29 leading female and male students.

title: The Zero Theory
summary: The program aims to help students create projects from scratch for a service or product, which will be developed through teatime meetings to discuss books on self-development and share ideas and new projects.

title: “Wanna Read” Program
summary: "Wanna Read" is a program created by Zayed University graduate, Sheikha Shamma bint Sultan bin Khalifa Al Nahyan. It provides an opportunity for the volunteers to read for children admitted to Khalifa Hospital. The program prepared a very warm and friendly environment that helps children recover. The Student Life Office at Zayed University is supporting the program by preparing a reading hall in one of the hospitals in the UAE, which will be launched by December 2016. This initiative comes in partnership with Sheikha Shamma bint Sultan Al Nahyan as part of her program “Wanna Read,” and the office will be collecting the funds to build the reading hall and prepare it for the children.

title: Reading Contest (by the International Club)
summary: The International Club launched a competition to encourage students to read. Students were asked to read a book, summarize it and present it using PowerPoint in a novel way or through a video or any other creative method.

title: Spring Charity Carnival at Zayed University "The White Hands"
summary: The Student Council on Abu Dhabi Campus organized a Spring Charity Carnival and donated the event’s income (from selling entrance tickets) to establish a library in one of the poor countries. The event was organized in cooperation with the Red Crescent Foundation.

title: The Human Library

It provides an opportunity for the volunteers to read for children admitted to Khalifa Hospital. The program prepared a very warm and friendly environment that helps children recover. The Student Life Office at Zayed University is supporting the program by preparing a reading hall in one of the hospitals in the UAE, which will be launched by December 2016. This initiative comes in partnership with Sheikha Shamma bint Sultan Al Nahyan as part of her program “Wanna Read,” and the office will be collecting the funds to build the reading hall and prepare it for the children.

title: Reading Contest (by the International Club)
summary: The International Club launched a competition to encourage students to read. Students were asked to read a book, summarize it and present it using PowerPoint in a novel way or through a video or any other creative method.

title: Spring Charity Carnival at Zayed University "The White Hands"
summary: The Student Council on Abu Dhabi Campus organized a Spring Charity Carnival and donated the event’s income (from selling entrance tickets) to establish a library in one of the poor countries. The event was organized in cooperation with the Red Crescent Foundation.

title: 100 Classic Books; a reading challenge
summary: The coordinator of the reading corner presents a list of classical books to the participants and encourages them to join a challenge in which they have to read 100 classical books in both Arabic and English in the reading corner; the participants present the books they read and discuss their topics.

title: "How to become a writer", a workshop organized by the International Club
summary: How to benefit from your writing skills and how to develop this hobby into a future profession; presented by the student and writer Muna Al Khatib.

title: The Best Company
summary: This is a reading corner on the University Promenade, during which a number of speakers were invited to encourage students to read, to exchange books and ideas and to discuss their opinions of the books they read.

title: The Human Library
summary: Members of the International Club at Zayed University in Abu Dhabi organized an event called "The Human Library", which was a panel to discuss an interesting book or a story or a personal experience that the participants wanted to share with the audience.

title: A Trip with Al-Jahith
summary: A workshop entitled "A Trip with Al-Jahith" was organized at Zayed University as a lecture delivered by Dr. Ali Al-Sharif, a Ph.D. holder in Arabic Literature from the World Islamic Sciences and Education University. The lecture discussed his works on literature, political history, morality, industry, women and other topics.

title: Emarati Authors
summary: The Emirati author Jamal Al Shehhi, founder of Kuttub Publishing House, delivered a lecture on the importance of reading books in Arabic and the significance of promoting the culture of reading for them in the community.

title: Promote the reading culture at your house
summary: A Faculty member from Zayed University's College of Education led a session with a group of students and discussed the topic of "why, when, and how to create a reading culture at home." The professor suggested a number of children’s stories and encouraged the parents to read to them.

title: Participation in Abu Dhabi International Book Fair
summary: Zayed University organized a workshop on the topic of reading and the path to academic success for parents of school and university students. It also included a cooperation with SeaCulture Foundation to perform a number of workshops for the audience on “How to make my child read”, "Vitamin D", "Mental Awakens", "Al-Jahith Literature", "Arabic Calligraphy", "How to read fast", and "How to analyze a movie adapted from a novel". The participation was concluded by the publishing of two books written by Zayed University graduates and another book by a current student.

title: The Open Day for families to discuss the importance of  Reading
summary: "How to Make your Children Fancy Reading" was an open day for families that offered a number of events such as a workshop on calligraphy, a reading corner for parents and children, and a section for donated books.

title: Fiction Story Competition (Kharareef)
summary: Fictional stories writing competition on Emirati culture for school students, in Arabic or English, reflecting forty themes chosen by the organizers’ committee of the competition. The winners were honored by Her Excellency Sheikha Lubna Al Qasimi.

title: Organizing seminars in the book club at the College of Humanities and Social Sciences:
summary: The "Book Club" is organizing a number of seminars led by college professors about the club's most important literary publications. The club is chaired by one of the college's faculty members in rotation, and students will select books to read individually. The books will not necessarily be from the curriculum of their college; however, the books chosen by the club are literary books and specialized magazines.

title: Poetry Session
summary: In the frame of the Reading Year Committee instructions at Zayed University, the department of the library and common learning is organizing a poetry session in November 2016, which coincides with the celebrations of UAE National Day. The session will be attended by a number of speakers, and there will be a number of other activities organized at the same time.

title: Reading at Home (Session in September 2016)
summary: A session was conducted by a Faculty member from the College of Education and organized by the Early Childhood Learning Center, addressing parents, faculty and students in the Center on the subject of “Reading at Home for your Children.” The session was also delivered by two students from the Early Childhood Learning Course EDC386.
